Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

---

In the meantime, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and cut the @Lime{1} into wedges. Drain and rinse the @Chickpeas{1%carton} in a sieve.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then separate the leaves. Cut any larger leaves in half lengthways down the middle.

---

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Add the pak choi and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g}. Stir-fry until just soft, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium-high, then stir in the @Red Thai Style Paste{50%g} and garlic. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

---

Stir the @Coconut Milk{200%ml}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and chickpeas into the sauce.

Bring to a boil, then lower the heat. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

---

While your sauce simmers, crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

When your rice is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Stir the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{32%g} and a squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge into the curry. Taste and season with salt, pepper or more lime juice if needed.

> Our Red Thai Style Veg Coconut Curry is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!

---

Share the zesty rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the Thai style veg curry.

Sprinkle over the peanuts and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!